title: Lovely necklace; good quality stones and presentation
text: This is perfect for gift giving in a nice box with a card explaining the healing properties of the stones. It's very well made and attractive. It is unisex in character, and also it is pretty long, so it would work fine for a man if he is not a big guy. I'm small and the necklace is longer than I usually wear, but it still has a nice feel and looks great. I've been feeling stressed and ungrounded lately and I find wearing tiger's eye and onyx really seems to be helpful. I love the bloodstone and Tibetan agate beads, although the latter appear composed. A lovely touch was the included smooth clear quartz with a little card explaining the properties of that stone, which I actually needed right now! I recommend this necklace highly. It's well made and unique.

title: Nice quality, well made bracelet, runs small
text: This is a nicely made bracelet. The cord material seems sturdy and the work is tidy. The beads are AAA quality, and although I have seen more strikingly colored tiger's eye, they are attractive. The blue tiger's eye is a nice addition, as it is more calming and grounding to the energizing qualities of yellow tiger's eye. The obsidian is deep and shiny. I like the 8mm beads over the larger ones, for comfort of wearing. This bracelet would only be suitable for a man with smaller or medium wrists, not large men. The bracelet has a very smooth and peaceful feel to it. It can be held or worn.

title: Adorable… if you NEVER wash it. EVER.
text:
I LOVE the design and was very excited to see it. However, you can NEVER wash what you iron it onto. EVER.

I washed it ONCE on the cold, delicate cycle, letting it air dry, and all the edges started to come off. I followed the directions and have never had problems iron-ing things on before. I still have some old tshirts I put iron-ons on 20-30 years ago that still are intact. This iron-on, however, couldn't stay on the t-shirt for even one wash. I washed in cold and my washer has a very good delicate cycle. I've washed 120+ year old quilts on cold/delicate in my washer, so I don't think my washer is to blame as it's a truly delicate wash. I didn't dry it, only one delicate wash cycle in cold water. I'm bummed it didn't last even one wash.

When my father passed away in 2018, he left all of his homemade wine to my brother, myself, and my stepmother.

So they've been slowly gathering in a corner of a spare room while worked out what to do with them. After visiting a local winery that boasted a wine bottle tree, I decided to go looking for my own.

I've been looking for just the right wine one for two years. One with enough branches to hold at least most of the bottles. One that wasn't stupidly expensive. This is that one.

Dad would be delighted and so am I.

title: One of the best oils for overall hair health
text: I started using this oil maybe 8 months ago.  My hair was thining and balding.  I visited the dermatologist and she recommended nutrafol and monoxil.  The monoxil seemed to be making the balding worst and also thining and stripping my locs.  The monoxil was also very sticky and greasy after a few applications and made the hair look dirty.  I was only applying it to the front and the front was getting worst.  This is when I told the dermatologist that I would use this oil instead and she agreed.  The oil smells like menthol and I would use it only at nights, but the smell can be soothing too.  The oil started to work, as my hair stopped stripping and began to fill back in with just the oil.  I used the monoxil for maybe 10 days in total and moved completely to the oil.  You can see from the photos how my hair continues to fill in.  I am so happy.  Grateful for this oil.  Prior to using it on my hair, I tried it on my eyebrows that weren't growing and my brows began to grow wild, this is the main reason I was encouraged to use it on my hair.  Give it at least 6 months to see results.  I would use nutrafol in concert with this oil.  Not sure of the integrity of the nutrafol here on Amazon so, either get it from their website or a dermatologist
